<subSubSection id="B4A62C97A08864246B3ED03E5C7A02D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B43ED97BC985F2833F4277B397588CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D74559E475BC55F086F49561B1D4A33D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Regional: Eastern margin of South Africa, off Richards Bay; 51 m. Elsewhere: Seychelles (van der 
<bibRefCitation id="DBA396EEB0775DFD4DDBCEBFAE433E42" author="Horst, van der C" journalOrPublisher="Coral Reefs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B132" refString="Horst, van der C, 1926. Madreporaria Eupsammidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London (Series 2, Zoology) 19(1): 43-53. https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1926.tb00540.x" title="Madreporaria Eupsammidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London (Series 2, Zoology) 19 (1): 43 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1926. tb 00540. x" year="1926">Horst 1926</bibRefCitation>
); Maldives (van der 
<bibRefCitation id="71F6E87BA65F89047EC57727E0241DC3" author="Horst, van der C" journalOrPublisher="Coral Reefs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B132" refString="Horst, van der C, 1926. Madreporaria Eupsammidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London (Series 2, Zoology) 19(1): 43-53. https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1926.tb00540.x" title="Madreporaria Eupsammidae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London (Series 2, Zoology) 19 (1): 43 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1926. tb 00540. x" year="1926">Horst 1926</bibRefCitation>
); off Sri Lanka (
<bibRefCitation id="A04D62F51445EEB0ADA1FFDFF70A6827" author="Alcock, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="138 - 149" refId="B4" refString="Alcock, A, 1893. On some newly-recorded corals from the Indian Seas. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 62 (2): 138 - 149" title="On some newly-recorded corals from the Indian Seas." volume="62" year="1893">Alcock 1893</bibRefCitation>
); Japan (
<bibRefCitation id="17E50D24AF823A3B121210437C880FD6" author="Eguchi, M" journalOrPublisher="JARE Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B85" refString="Eguchi, M, 1968. The Hydrocorals and Scleractinian Corals of Sagami Bay collected by his Majesty the Emperor of Japan. Maruzen Co., Ltd., Tokyo, [xv +] 221 pp." title="The Hydrocorals and Scleractinian Corals of Sagami Bay collected by his Majesty the Emperor of Japan. Maruzen Co., Ltd., Tokyo, [xv +] 221 pp." year="1968">Eguchi 1968</bibRefCitation>
<bibRefCitation id="9A73957337B1886DE14E6CF3764DEE38" author="Cairns, S" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 150" refId="B37" refString="Cairns, S, 1994. Scleractinia of the temperate North Pacific. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 557: 1 - 150" title="Scleractinia of the temperate North Pacific." volume="557" year="1994">; Cairns 1994</bibRefCitation>
<bibRefCitation id="810B533F1957B0ABAC71EB4B41B65504" author="Tachikawa, H" journalOrPublisher="Kuroshio Biosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 27" refId="B275" refString="Tachikawa, H, 2005. Azooxanthellate Scleractinia (Hexacorallia, Anthozoa, Cnidria) collected from Otsuki, Kochi Prefecture, Japan. Kuroshio Biosphere 2: 1 - 27" title="Azooxanthellate Scleractinia (Hexacorallia, Anthozoa, Cnidria) collected from Otsuki, Kochi Prefecture, Japan." volume="2" year="2005">; Tachikawa 2005</bibRefCitation>
); 14-59 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44D128DEDD50EA2A2D4C5F159737D502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F6EFFF4F90021C858C9998674746FBB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A9700C6E2A11131B61B78180DC0D35F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
No new records of 
<taxonomicName id="B0F66B8808152998C022D94FCBDF03A6" authorityName="Cairns" authorityYear="2001" class="Anthozoa" family="Dendrophylliidae" genus="Balanophyllia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balanophyllia (B.) vanderhorsti" order="Scleractinia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="vanderhorsti" subGenus="B.">Balanophyllia (B.) vanderhorsti</taxonomicName>
were examined during the present study. Therefore, the occurrence of this species in South Africa is based solely on previous published records. 
<bibRefCitation id="D365E3484DDD61444276C0CC3A143231" author="Boshoff, P" journalOrPublisher="Investigational Report" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B21" refString="Boshoff, P, 1981. An annotated checklist of southern African Scleractinia. South African Association for Marine Biological Research, Oceanographic Research Institute, Durban. Investigational Report 49: 1 - 45" title="An annotated checklist of southern African Scleractinia. South African Association for Marine Biological Research, Oceanographic Research Institute, Durban." volume="49" year="1981">
<normalizedToken id="F558A05DEBD1D02FA00D7BA70D46785D" originalValue="Boshoffâ€™s">Boshoff's</normalizedToken>
(1981)
</bibRefCitation>
record of 
<taxonomicName id="6D0270FCBF44DB17383C5A072D93A0F7" genus="B." lsidName="B. vanderhorsti" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="vanderhorsti">
<emphasis id="FA5B5106A98027E6DCFF0ADD217241A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. vanderhorsti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(reported as 
<taxonomicName id="E9E88F52171C0A40B302317E18C34C2E" genus="B." lsidName="B. ponderosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ponderosa">
<emphasis id="552C17C82E51098E0130E342F31B7210" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. ponderosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which is a junior homonym)) has basal stolons and therefore represents 
<taxonomicName id="C76B519AC56CED291A3B0BD00616E687" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1870" class="Anthozoa" family="Dendrophylliidae" genus="Rhizopsammia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhizopsammia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BF01A70376F0397B4AE5934522E568FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhizopsammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Verrill, 1870. To reiterate, 
<bibRefCitation id="47B3BBFDA83D31FA26AB87D6F2C40F70" author="Cairns, S" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="213 - 292" refId="B50" refString="Cairns, S, Keller, N, 1993. New taxa distributional records of azooxanthellate Scleractinia (Cnidaria, Anthozoa) from the tropical southwest Indian Ocean, with comments on their zoogeography and ecology. Annals of the South African Museum 103 (5): 213 - 292" title="New taxa distributional records of azooxanthellate Scleractinia (Cnidaria, Anthozoa) from the tropical southwest Indian Ocean, with comments on their zoogeography and ecology." volume="103" year="1993">Cairns and Keller (1993)</bibRefCitation>
observed that this South African species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="EB3FB8255C15FBE832CB30A06DC3022B" genus="B." lsidName="B. regalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="regalis">
<emphasis id="5325F3640B90B4F8DA1EC683B1A53B55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. regalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Alcock, 1893) in lacking an epitheca.
</paragraph>
